		<title>Values in Design</title>
		<link>http://evoke.ics.uci.edu/values-in-design/</link>
		<comments>http://evoke.ics.uci.edu/values-in-design/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Sun, 13 Jan 2013 20:25:18 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Courtney Loder]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Research]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://vid-web0.ics.uci.edu/?p=173</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[We host an annual workshop which brings together graduate students and faculty from a wide-ranging array of fields with the purpose of creating a shared theoretical basis and practice for values-centered design.The Values in Design Doctoral Workshop is a week-long, intensive event sponsored by the Values in Design Program through the Department of Informatics in(...)]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>We host an annual workshop which brings together graduate students and faculty from a wide-ranging array of fields with the purpose of creating a shared theoretical basis and practice for values-centered design.The Values in Design Doctoral Workshop is a week-long, intensive event sponsored by the Values in Design Program through the Department of Informatics in the Donald Bren School of Information &amp; Computer Sciences at University of California, Irvine.</p>
<p>We bring together a group of exceptional doctoral students from a wide range of backgrounds to study and address issues of how human and social values are embedded, built into, influence, and otherwise instantiate themselves in information systems and technologies. By working across the intersections of computer science and engineering, social studies of science and technology, anthropology, policy and law, business, social entrepreneurship, art, design, and information science, the group delves into the theories contributing to (and arising out of) sociotechnical design, in addition to spending the week designing and building original information systems and technologies that materialize a set of social values.</p>
<p>If you would like to know more about the workshop, or more generally about the work being done in the Values in Design Program, please send an email to vid@ics.uci.edu.</p>
<p><br/></p>
