		<title>Emerging Configurations</title>
		<link>http://evoke.ics.uci.edu/emerging-configurations/</link>
		<comments>http://evoke.ics.uci.edu/emerging-configurations/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Sun, 13 Jan 2013 18:22:47 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Courtney Loder]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Research]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://vid-web0.ics.uci.edu/?p=162</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Linear text and the technology of the book has gotten us pretty far, and we owe a lot to it, but it&#8217;s time to loosen our death-grip on the authority of text and play with the amazing interactive environments at our disposal&#8230;and figure out what it means to do great scholarship and express ourselves in(...)]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Linear text and the technology of the book has gotten us pretty far, and we owe a lot to it, but it&#8217;s time to loosen our death-grip on the authority of text and play with the amazing interactive environments at our disposal&#8230;and figure out what it means to do great scholarship and express ourselves in new modalities.</p>
<p>There are so many more interesting, interactive, informative, aesthetically pleasing, and playful ways to create and communicate knowledge. Databases are scholarship. Powerpoint presentations are chock-full of our ideas. Visualizations can sometimes inform better in one glance than 20 pages of explanation.</p>
<p><img src='http://vid-web0.ics.uci.edu/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/econfigs_txt.jpg'></p>]]></content:encoded>
